This paper primarily focuses on the security and privacy concerns related to illegal live streaming services, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the tracking techniques used by these services, which could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper explores the use of fingerprinting techniques, which could be classified under cybernetics (cs.CY) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
